reviews.title: Always good and place.
reviews.text: Eating here more often, Chinese maid is fast and very friendly and very skilled. Good and normal portions and tasty dishes. Definitely recommended.

reviews.title: Takeout
reviews.text:
Ordered a migroon and chicken.
And a spring roll, too.
The latter tastes good, by the way.
Chicken grouse is a drama.
Grouse but no chicken.
Boss says that's the way it should be.
There's just no chicken in it.
You wouldn't believe that.
Next time to International in Almelo!!!!!

reviews.title: Everything was GREAT 👍
reviews.text:
Super yummy food. Real good quality. 
The restaurant is really clean and spacious. 
We really enjoyed it and will definitely be back here!
🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟

reviews.title: Small portions and not hot
reviews.text:
Jasmingarden is our regular Chinese restaurant where we often take away.
Always good, with the occasional mistake.
Yesterday we decided to have dinner in the restaurant after a bike ride.
Upon entering we had to wait a few minutes before waiting staff arrived.
On the menu we could not find what we wanted to eat, that was bamirames special and mifang with chicken.
Despite it not being on the menu they could serve it.
Bamirames special I always eat at a Chinese restaurant, it consists of a bowl of bami and various trays with side dishes, including chicken.
This time everything was served on a plate, the chicken was missing.
The mifang was also served on a plate. 
They were small portions and because all sides had to be on the plate there was only little bami.
Furthermore, both the bamirames and the mifang were not well warm and very lax.
Very disappointing because we expected a lot from this restaurant.

reviews.title: Not satisfied, how bad....
reviews.text:
Removed Thaptjoi with shrimps and noodles.
Hi, just got thaptjoi with shrimps.
There were 5 small shrimps in a lot. Touge and almost no other vegetables and no taste to it.
The noodles only had some Chinese cabbage in it
And that for 22 euros.
Never go here again, not the first time things are not right.

reviews.title: Mediocre
reviews.text: Mediocre quality food for the price. Certainly does not exceed the all you can eat restaurants. We work a lot with sauces. Furthermore, surimi was served instead of crab and there was plastic in the lettuce. This used to be a really good restaurant but unfortunately not anymore.

reviews.title: Never again
reviews.text:
Tomato soup was very watery, thin and not filling.
Foe yong hai had no taste. Spring roll not great either.

reviews.title: Not recommended.
reviews.text:
We ordered food to eat at home. 6 pieces of sushi at €15.60 WOW and a small rice table. Meat was bland and flat. We are shocked at the price of over €100!!!! They also serve small bowls with the rice table.
Babi adjam meat was burnt. And the rest wasn't great.
Next time we will drive to Hengelo! These prices are really antisocial.

reviews.title: Not again
reviews.text:
We had a rice table, except for the chicken in gong bao sauce, everything was flat and bland in taste. The starter, the mini spring rolls, were too soft, not crispy. There is no menu for children. They prepared chicken nuggets with fries. Fine! But then they ask €21 for it!! I think that is very expensive, especially compared to other restaurants that have a large and extensive offering for children and charge much less for it.
The 2 girls in the service are too busy. As a result, structure is lacking. For example, it took a very long time to clear the table. They are friendly!
Shame! All in all, not worth repeating for us.

reviews.title: Decent Food Big Bill
reviews.text: We had a nice dinner over a 2 1/2 hours. The food was good quality the service was excellent but it could be over priced.  It's a plus that the chef preforms the majority of the final cooking Infront of you, the negative is that most of the food is cooked on a large griddle. Which in it's self limits the variety of food available. So it's not a place that I would frequent even if it were close.

reviews.title: Good Show! Great Salmon!
reviews.text:
The japanese chefs here put on a fun cooking shot - even though they must do it over and over, they seem to still be having fun with it!

DO NO order the biggest menu, it is SO MUCH FOOD, we walked away sick (our own fault!)

Of our 7 or so courses, 2-3 were excellent, 2-3 OK, and 2-3 not great

Its a little pricey, but you pay for the cook cooking show...

reviews.title: Take away with family
reviews.text: We were a family party and had a take away delivered to the home. Four big hungry boys, four adults and a small girl with a good appetite were all very well fed! Plenty of choice on the menu, everything piping hot, tasty and fresh. I wish we had this quality of take away close to our own home!

reviews.title: Great Chinese Food in Netherlands
reviews.text: One of lunch we decide to have Chinese food, our partners recommended this restaurant and it does not disappoint. The cooking style is Asian and it suits our taste. Was surprise that this Gem is located at a outskirt of the major city. We have a great meal.

reviews.title: Best ever
reviews.text: So we had a company dinner in here....really wonderful! ! You get your lovely meal just cooked around you with a special taste and extremely good quality.  Clean, best service and Great quality food will jump your mouth to a special level never tryed before. Funtastic! !!

reviews.title: Excellent sushis, long waiting time in the restaurant
reviews.text:
My kids insisted on going to that restaurant, because they have heard about the sushi's; apparently, they were not disappointed, however it took more that 3 hours to complete a normal 3 courses menu, while they were only 2 tables of 6 in the restaurant...I would recommend going for the take away rather that the restaurant, just for this reason.
Service was good, professional and very friendly.

articleContent.title: Celebrate the best of Osaka’s food and nightlife with Suntory

seoInfo.metaDescription: If you’ve ever found yourself standing in line for hours at a famous ramen spot in Japan, you’d probably agree that food and drinks are a big part of why we travel. It’s one of the best ways to get a glimpse into a destination's culture, traditions, and history, whether it’s through its local dishes, ingredients, or culinary customs. But if you really want to embrace local culture, there’s no better way than over a glass. Share a drink with locals, friends, and fellow travelers, and experience the camaraderie, stories, and traditions that make up the heart of a destination, forging deeper connections along the way.

articleContent.title: A food lover’s guide to North Myrtle Beach

seoInfo.metaDescription: Whether it’s shoulder season or summer’s peak, you’ll always find delicious dishes at North Myrtle Beach. Dine by the waterfront after a balmy beach day, eat like the locals at treasured hotspots, or take the family out for a celebratory meal. Whatever you crave in an unforgettable vacation, you’re sure to find it here in this must-read roundup of top restaurants.

reviews.title: Chinese/Japanees Restaurant the Dutch way
reviews.text: I was here eating solo, due to the chines character i was expecting some sort of table with different dishes. But that is for 2 people or more. So i choice one dish and that is the Peking Duck with BBQ sauce, witch was delicious. It was a nice restaurant with nice waiters.
